article.headline: Kent State 67, Ohio 65 (OT)
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Omni Smith scored 13 points, including the winning jumper with four seconds left in overtime, to lead Kent State to a 67-65 victory over Ohio on Sunday. Armon Gates and Haminn Quaintance also had 13 points apiece for the Golden Flashes (9-7, 2-1 Mid-American Conference), and Quaintance added 13 rebounds. Ohio (11-5, 2-1) tied the score at 57 on a tip-in from Leon Williams with 1:20 left in regulation, and Smith and Quaintance both missed shots in the final minute that could have given Kent State the win. A layup and foul shot from Quaintance put the Golden Flashes ahead 65-62 with 37 seconds left in overtime, but Bubba Walther hit a 3-pointer for the Bobcats to tie the score for the 13th time of the game. Smith hit a jumper with four seconds left and Ohio's Whitney Davis missed a 3-point attempt in the final second. Jerome Tillman led the Bobcats with 20 points on 8-of-10 shooting and had 17 rebounds, Sonny Troutman added 13 points and Walther had 12. Williams had 10 points and nine rebounds for Ohio. The Bobcats outrebounded the Golden Flashes 47-37, and shot 39.3 percent (24-of-61) compared with Kent State's 38.2 percent (26-of-68). Kent State scored 22 points off 22 Ohio turnovers.
